  13        """
  14        Initialize the LatexMaker instance with default colors and path.

  17        self.latexFinal = ""
  18        self.colors = ["skyblue", "cyan", "brightmaroon", "SQLCodeGreen", "SQLcodegray", "SQLCodePurple"]
  19        self.path = "../../Assets/LatexFiles/"
  20        self.defineColor = """\\definecolor{skyblue}{rgb}{0.53, 0.81, 0.92}

  34    def render(self):
  35        """
  36        Save the final LaTeX code to a file.
  37        """
  38        print(self.path)
  39        with open(self.path, 'w') as file:
  40            file.write(self.latexCode)

  42    def getData(self, path):
  43        """
  44        Read and parse a JSON file containing execution time data.
  45
  46        :param path: Path to the JSON file.
  47        :return: Tuple (timeDict, maxRows, maxTime)
  48        """
  49        with open(path, 'r') as file:
  50            data = json.load(file)
  51        timeDict = data.get("time_data", {})
  52        maxRows = data.get("max_rows", 0)
  53        maxTime = data.get("max_time", 0)
  54        return timeDict, maxRows, maxTime
  55
  56    def get_rgb_value(self, color_name):
  57        """
  58        Return the RGB or HTML value for a given color name.
  59
  60        :param color_name: Name of the color.
  61        :return: Tuple (color value, color format).
  62        """
  63        color_map = {
  64            "brightmaroon": ("195,33,72", "RGB"),
  65            "cyan": ("0,255,255", "RGB"),
  66            "skyblue": ("135,206,235", "RGB"),
  67            "SQLCodeGreen": ("006400", "HTML"),
  68            "SQLcodegray": ("7F7F7F", "HTML"),
  69            "SQLCodePurple": ("C42043", "HTML"),
  70        }
  71        return color_map.get(color_name, ("0,0,0", "RGB"))

  73    def prepareComparisonData(self, jsonPaths, attributes=[3, 6, 9]):
  74        """
  75        Prepare time data for comparison plots.
  76
  77        :param jsonPaths: List of paths to JSON files.
  78        :param attributes: List of attributes to consider (default [3, 6, 9]).
  79        :return: (timeDicts, maxRowsList, maxTimeList)
  80        """
  81        timeDicts = []
  82        all_max_rows = []
  83        all_times_per_attr = [[] for _ in attributes]
  84
  85        for path in jsonPaths:
  86            timeDict, maxRows, _ = self.getData(path)
  87            timeDict = {int(k): v for k, v in timeDict.items()}
  88            timeDicts.append(timeDict)
  89            all_max_rows.append(max(timeDict.keys()))
  90
  91            for i in range(len(attributes)):
  92                print(len(attributes))
  93                all_times_per_attr[i].extend(
  94                    timeDict[k][i] for k in timeDict
  95                )
  96
  97        maxRowsList = [max(all_max_rows)] * len(attributes)
  98        maxTimeList = [max(times) for times in all_times_per_attr]
  99
 100        return timeDicts, maxRowsList, maxTimeList

 102    def roundToNearestN(value, n):
 103        """
 104        Round the given value to the nearest multiple of (n-1).
 105
 106        :param value: The value to round.
 107        :param n: The reference number; rounding is done to a multiple of (n-1).
 108        :return: The rounded value.
 109        """
 110        if value == 0:
 111            return 0
 112        return round(value / (n - 1)) * (n - 1)

 114    def twoAlgoComparaison369Latex(self, timeDict1, timeDict2, maxRowsList, maxTimeList, algo1, algo2,
 115                                   latexFilePath="", scaleX=280, scaleY=280, attributes=[3, 6, 9]):
 116        """
 117        Generate clean and well-indented LaTeX code to compare two algorithms across multiple attributes
 118        (typically for 3, 6, and 9 attributes), with linear scaling for axes.
 119
 120        :param timeDict1: Time dictionary for the first algorithm.
 121        :param timeDict2: Time dictionary for the second algorithm.
 122        :param maxRowsList: List containing the maximum cardinality for each attribute configuration.
 123        :param maxTimeList: List containing the maximum execution time for each attribute configuration.
 124        :param algo1: Enum member (AlgoEnum) representing the first algorithm to compare.
 125        :param algo2: Enum member (AlgoEnum) representing the second algorithm to compare.
 126        :param latexFilePath: Path to save the generated LaTeX file (relative or absolute).
 127        :param scaleX: Width of the graph in points (default is 280pt).
 128        :param scaleY: Height of the graph in points (default is 280pt).
 129        :param attributes: List of attribute counts to compare (default is [3, 6, 9]).
 130        """
 131        self.path += latexFilePath
 132        algo1_name = algo1.value[0]
 133        algo2_name = algo2.value[0]
 134
 135        # Define color styles
 136        color_styles = []
 137        for i, color in enumerate(self.colors[:2]):
 138            rgb = self.get_rgb_value(color)
 139            color_styles.append(f"\\definecolor{{{color}}}{{RGB}}{{{rgb}}}")
 140            color_styles.append(
 141                f"\\tikzset{{big{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},"
 142                f"\nsmall{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}}}"
 143            )
 144
 145        latex_lines = [
 146            r"\documentclass[tikz, border=10pt]{standalone}",
 147            r"\usepackage{tikz}",
 148            r"\usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta, shapes, positioning}",
 149            r"\usepackage{xcolor}",
 150            *color_styles,
 151            r"\begin{document}"
 152        ]
 153
 154        for i in range(len(attributes)):
 155            maxTime = roundtoNearestThousand(maxTimeList[i])  # Round maxTime to nearest thousand
 156            print(maxTime)
 157
 158            ratioX = scaleX / maxRowsList[i]
 159            ratioY = scaleY / maxTime
 160
 161            # Algo 1 line and points
 162            line1 = f"\\draw[{self.colors[0]}, line width=2pt]"
 163            points1 = []
 164            for k in sorted(timeDict1.keys()):
 165                x = int(round(k * ratioX))
 166                y = int(round(timeDict1[k][i] * ratioY * 0.8))
 167                line1 += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 168                points1.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={self.colors[0]}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 169            line1 = line1.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 170
 171            # Algo 2 line and points
 172            line2 = f"\\draw[{self.colors[1]}, line width=2pt]"
 173            points2 = []
 174            for k in sorted(timeDict2.keys()):
 175                x = int(round(k * ratioX))
 176                y = int(round(timeDict2[k][i] * ratioY * 0.8))
 177                line2 += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 178                points2.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={self.colors[1]}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 179            line2 = line2.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 180
 181            # Axes graduations
 182            x_axis = "        \\foreach \\x/\\xtext in {\n"
 183            for step in [scaleX * s / 5 for s in range(6)]:
 184                value = roundtoNearestTen(maxRowsList[i] * (step / scaleX))
 185                x_axis += f"            {roundtoNearestTen(step)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 186            x_axis = (x_axis.rstrip(", \n")
 187                      + "} {\n"
 188                      + "            \\draw (\\x, 2pt) -- (\\x, -2pt) node[below] {\\xtext\\strut};\n"
 189                      + "        }")
 190
 191            y_axis = "        \\foreach \\y/\\ytext in {\n"
 192            for step in [scaleY * s / 5 for s in range(5)]:
 193                adjusted_value = roundtoNearestTen(maxTime * (step / (scaleY * 0.8)))
 194                y_axis += f"            {roundtoNearestTen(step)}pt/${adjusted_value}$, \n"
 195            y_axis = (y_axis.rstrip(", \n")
 196                      + "} {\n"
 197                      + "            \\draw (2pt, \\y) -- (-2pt, \\y) node[left] {\\ytext\\strut};\n"
 198                      + "        }")
 199
 200            tikz_block = [
 201                f"    % Graph for {attributes[i]} attributes",
 202                r"    \begin{tikzpicture}[",
 203                f"        line join=bevel,",
 204                f"        big{self.colors[0]}node/.style={{shape=circle, fill={self.colors[0]}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},",
 205                f"        big{self.colors[1]}node/.style={{shape=circle, fill={self.colors[1]}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},",
 206                f"        small{self.colors[0]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[0]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}},",
 207                f"        small{self.colors[1]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[1]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}",
 208                r"    ]",
 209                r"        % Axes",
 210                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- ({scaleX}pt, 0pt) node[anchor=north west] {{Cardinality}};",
 211                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- (0pt, {scaleY}pt) node[anchor=south] {{Response time in s}};",
 212                r"        % Axis graduation",
 213                x_axis,
 214                y_axis,
 215                r"        % Lines",
 216                f"        {line1}",
 217                f"        {line2}",
 218                r"        % Points",
 219                *["        " + pt for pt in points1],
 220                *["        " + pt for pt in points2],
 221                r"        % Caption",
 222                r"        \matrix [below left] at (current bounding box.north east) {",
 223                f"            \\node [small{self.colors[0]}node, label=right:{algo1_name} with {attributes[i]} attributes] {{}}; \\\\",
 224                f"            \\node [small{self.colors[1]}node, label=right:{algo2_name} with {attributes[i]} attributes] {{}}; \\\\",
 225                r"        };",
 226                r"    \end{tikzpicture}"
 227            ]
 228
 229            latex_lines.extend(tikz_block)
 230
 231        latex_lines.append(r"\end{document}")
 232        self.latexCode = "\n".join(latex_lines)
 233        self.addLatexCode(self.latexCode)
 234        self.render()

 236    def twoAlgoComparaison369LatexLog(self, timeDict1, timeDict2, maxRowsList, maxTimeList, algo1, algo2,
 237                                      latexFilePath="", scaleX=280, scaleY=280, attributes=[3, 6, 9],
 238                                      scaleType="LinX/LinY"):
 239        """
 240        Generate LaTeX code to compare two algorithms across multiple attributes (3, 6, 9),
 241        with optional logarithmic or linear scaling on the X and/or Y axes.
 242
 243        :param timeDict1: Time dictionary for the first algorithm.
 244        :param timeDict2: Time dictionary for the second algorithm.
 245        :param maxRowsList: List of maximum cardinalities (number of rows) for each attribute.
 246        :param maxTimeList: List of maximum execution times for each attribute.
 247        :param algo1: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the first algorithm.
 248        :param algo2: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the second algorithm.
 249        :param latexFilePath: Path where the LaTeX output file will be saved.
 250        :param scaleX: Width of the plot in points (default 280).
 251        :param scaleY: Height of the plot in points (default 280).
 252        :param attributes: List of attributes (typically [3, 6, 9]) to generate the plots for.
 253        :param scaleType: Scaling type for axes, can be "LinX/LinY", "LogX/LinY", "LinX/LogY", or "LogX/LogY".
 254        """
 255        self.path += latexFilePath
 256        algo1_name = algo1.value[0]
 257        algo2_name = algo2.value[0]
 258
 259        # Define color styles
 260        color_styles = []
 261        for i, color in enumerate(self.colors[:2]):
 262            rgb = self.get_rgb_value(color)
 263            color_styles.append(f"\\definecolor{{{color}}}{{RGB}}{{{rgb}}}")
 264            color_styles.append(
 265                f"\\tikzset{{big{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},"
 266                f"small{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}}}"
 267            )
 268
 269        latex_lines = [
 270            r"\documentclass[tikz, border=10pt]{standalone}",
 271            r"\usepackage{tikz}",
 272            r"\usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta, shapes, positioning}",
 273            r"\usepackage{xcolor}",
 274            *color_styles,
 275            r"\begin{document}"
 276        ]
 277
 278        for i in range(len(attributes)):
 279            maxTime = roundtoNearestThousand(maxTimeList[i])  # Round maxTime to nearest thousand
 280            print(maxTime)
 281
 282            # Set the scaling type
 283            is_log_x = 'LogX' in scaleType
 284            is_log_y = 'LogY' in scaleType
 285
 286            # Calculate scaling ratios based on the chosen scale type
 287            if is_log_x:
 288                ratioX = scaleX / math.log(maxRowsList[i] + 1)  # Logarithmic scale for X
 289            else:
 290                ratioX = scaleX / maxRowsList[i]  # Linear scale for X
 291
 292            if is_log_y:
 293                ratioY = scaleY / math.log(maxTime + 1)  # Logarithmic scale for Y
 294            else:
 295                ratioY = scaleY / maxTime  # Linear scale for Y
 296
 297            # Algo 1 line and points
 298            line1 = f"\\draw[{self.colors[0]}, line width=2pt]"
 299            points1 = []
 300            for k in sorted(timeDict1.keys()):
 301                x = int(round(math.log(k + 1) * ratioX)) if is_log_x else int(round(k * ratioX))
 302                y = int(round(math.log(timeDict1[k][i] + 1) * ratioY)) if is_log_y else int(
 303                    round(timeDict1[k][i] * ratioY))
 304                line1 += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 305                points1.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={self.colors[0]}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 306            line1 = line1.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 307
 308            # Algo 2 line and points
 309            line2 = f"\\draw[{self.colors[1]}, line width=2pt]"
 310            points2 = []
 311            for k in sorted(timeDict2.keys()):
 312                x = int(round(math.log(k + 1) * ratioX)) if is_log_x else int(round(k * ratioX))
 313                y = int(round(math.log(timeDict2[k][i] + 1) * ratioY)) if is_log_y else int(
 314                    round(timeDict2[k][i] * ratioY))
 315                line2 += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 316                points2.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={self.colors[1]}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 317            line2 = line2.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 318
 319            # Axes graduations
 320            x_axis = "        \\foreach \\x/\\xtext in {\n"
 321            if is_log_x:
 322                log_steps = [math.log(s + 1) for s in range(0, maxRowsList[i] + 1, maxRowsList[i] // 5)]
 323                for step in log_steps:
 324                    value = roundtoNearestTen(math.exp(step))
 325                    x_axis += f"            {int(step * ratioX)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 326            else:
 327                for step in [scaleX * s / 5 for s in range(6)]:
 328                    value = roundtoNearestTen(maxRowsList[i] * (step / scaleX))
 329                    x_axis += f"            {int(step)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 330            x_axis = (x_axis.rstrip(", \n")
 331                      + "} {\n"
 332                      + "            \\draw (\\x, 2pt) -- (\\x, -2pt) node[below, font=\\small] {\\xtext\\strut};\n"
 333                      + "        }")
 334
 335            y_axis = "        \\foreach \\y/\\ytext in {\n"
 336            if is_log_y:
 337                log_steps = [math.log(s + 1) for s in range(0, maxTime + 1, maxTime // 5)]
 338                for step in log_steps:
 339                    adjusted_value = roundtoNearestTen(math.exp(step))
 340                    y_axis += f"            {int(step * ratioY)}pt/${adjusted_value}$, \n"
 341            else:
 342                for step in [scaleY * s / 5 for s in range(5)]:
 343                    adjusted_value = round(maxTime * (step / (scaleY * 0.8)), 2)
 344                    y_axis += f"            {int(step)}pt/${adjusted_value}$, \n"
 345            y_axis = (y_axis.rstrip(", \n")
 346                      + "} {\n"
 347                      + "            \\draw (2pt, \\y) -- (-2pt, \\y) node[left, font=\\small] {\\ytext\\strut};\n"
 348                      + "        }")

 352                r"    \begin{tikzpicture}[",
 353                f"        line join=bevel,",
 354                f"        big{self.colors[0]}node/.style={{shape=circle, fill={self.colors[0]}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},",
 355                f"        big{self.colors[1]}node/.style={{shape=circle, fill={self.colors[1]}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},",
 356                f"        small{self.colors[0]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[0]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}},",
 357                f"        small{self.colors[1]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[1]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}",
 358                r"    ]",
 359                r"        % Axes",

 361                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- (0pt, {scaleY}pt) node[anchor=south, font=\\large] {{Response time in s}};",
 362                r"        % Axis graduation",

 389    def threeAlgoComparaison369LatexLog(self, timeDict1, timeDict2, timeDict3, maxRowsList, maxTimeList, algo1, algo2,
 390                                        algo3,
 391                                        latexFilePath="", scaleX=280, scaleY=280, attributes=[3, 6, 9],
 392                                        scaleType="LinX/LinY"):
 393        """
 394        Generate LaTeX code to compare three algorithms across multiple attributes
 395        with optional logarithmic scaling for X and/or Y axes.
 396
 397        :param timeDict1: Time dictionary for the first algorithm.
 398        :param timeDict2: Time dictionary for the second algorithm.
 399        :param timeDict3: Time dictionary for the third algorithm.
 400        :param maxRowsList: List of maximum row counts per attribute (3, 6, 9).
 401        :param maxTimeList: List of maximum execution times per attribute (3, 6, 9).
 402        :param algo1: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the first algorithm.
 403        :param algo2: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the second algorithm.
 404        :param algo3: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the third algorithm.
 405        :param latexFilePath: Output path where the generated LaTeX file will be saved.
 406        :param scaleX: Width of the generated graph (in pt, default 280).
 407        :param scaleY: Height of the generated graph (in pt, default 280).
 408        :param attributes: List of attributes to generate graphs for (default [3, 6, 9]).
 409        :param scaleType: Type of scaling on X and Y axes ("LinX/LinY", "LogX/LinY", "LinX/LogY", or "LogX/LogY").
 410        """
 411
 412        self.path += latexFilePath
 413        algo_names = [algo1.value[0], algo2.value[0], algo3.value[0]]
 414        timeDicts = [timeDict1, timeDict2, timeDict3]
 415
 416        # Define color styles
 417        color_styles = []
 418        for i, color in enumerate(self.colors[:3]):
 419            color_value, color_format = self.get_rgb_value(color)
 420            color_styles.append(f"\\definecolor{{{color}}}{{{color_format}}}{{{color_value}}}")
 421            color_styles.append(
 422                f"\\tikzset{{big{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},"
 423                f"small{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}}}"
 424            )
 425
 426        latex_lines = [
 427            r"\documentclass[tikz, border=10pt]{standalone}",
 428            r"\usepackage{tikz}",
 429            r"\usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta, shapes, positioning}",
 430            r"\usepackage{xcolor}",
 431            *color_styles,
 432            r"\begin{document}"
 433        ]
 434
 435        # Determine scaling type
 436        is_log_x = 'LogX' in scaleType
 437        is_log_y = 'LogY' in scaleType
 438
 439        for i, attr in enumerate(attributes):
 440            maxRows = maxRowsList[i]
 441
 442            maxTime = roundtoNearestThousand(maxTimeList[i])
 443
 444            ratioX = scaleX / math.log(maxRows + 1) if is_log_x else scaleX / maxRows
 445            ratioY = scaleY / math.log(maxTime + 1) if is_log_y else scaleY / maxTime
 446
 447            # Generate lines and points
 448            lines = []
 449            points = []
 450            for j, timeDict in enumerate(timeDicts):
 451                color = self.colors[j]
 452                line = f"\\draw[{color}, line width=2pt]"
 453                point_set = []
 454                for k in sorted(timeDict.keys()):
 455                    x = int(round(math.log(k + 1) * ratioX)) if is_log_x else int(round(k * ratioX))
 456                    yval = timeDict[k][i]
 457                    y = int(round(math.log(yval + 1) * ratioY)) if is_log_y else int(round(yval * ratioY))
 458                    line += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 459                    point_set.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={color}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 460                line = line.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 461                lines.append(line)
 462                points.append(point_set)
 463
 464            # X axis graduations
 465            x_axis = "        \\foreach \\x/\\xtext in {\n"
 466            if is_log_x:
 467                log_steps = [math.log(s + 1) for s in range(0, maxRows + 1, max(1, maxRows // 5))]
 468                for step in log_steps:
 469                    value = roundtoNearestTen(math.exp(step))
 470                    x_axis += f"            {int(step * ratioX)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 471            else:
 472                for step in [scaleX * s / 5 for s in range(6)]:
 473                    value = roundtoNearestTen(maxRows * (step / scaleX))
 474                    x_axis += f"            {int(step)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 475            x_axis = (
 476                    x_axis.rstrip(", \n") +
 477                    "} {\n            \\draw (\\x, 2pt) -- (\\x, -2pt) node[below, font=\\small] {\\xtext\\strut};\n        }"
 478            )
 479
 480            # Y axis graduations
 481            y_axis = "        \\foreach \\y/\\ytext in {\n"
 482            if is_log_y:
 483                log_steps = [math.log(s + 1) for s in range(0, maxTime + 1, max(1, maxTime // 5))]
 484                for step in log_steps:
 485                    value = roundtoNearestTen(math.exp(step))
 486                    y_axis += f"            {int(step * ratioY)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 487            else:
 488                for step in [scaleY * s / 5 for s in range(6)]:
 489                    adjusted_value = round(maxTime * (step / (scaleY * 0.8)), 2)
 490                    y_axis += f"            {int(step)}pt/${adjusted_value}$, \n"
 491            y_axis = (
 492                    y_axis.rstrip(", \n") +
 493                    "} {\n            \\draw (2pt, \\y) -- (-2pt, \\y) node[left, font=\\small] {\\ytext\\strut};\n        }"
 494            )
 495
 496            tikz_block = [
 497                f"    % Graph for {attr} attributes",
 498                r"    \begin{tikzpicture}[",
 499                r"        line join=bevel,",
 500                *[
 501                    f"        small{self.colors[j]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[j]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}},"
 502                    for j in range(3)
 503                ],
 504                r"    ]",
 505                r"        % Axes",
 506                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- ({scaleX}pt, 0pt) node[anchor=north west, yshift=15pt] {{Cardinality}};",
 507                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- (0pt, {scaleY}pt) node[anchor=south, font=\\large] {{Response time in s}};",
 508                r"        % Axis graduation",
 509                x_axis,
 510                y_axis,
 511                r"        % Lines",
 512                *["        " + l for l in lines],
 513                r"        % Points",
 514                *[f"        {pt}" for point_set in points for pt in point_set],
 515                r"        % Caption",
 516                r"        \matrix [draw=none, fill=white, fill opacity=0.7, text opacity=1,",
 517                r"                 above right=0.5cm and 0cm of current bounding box.north west,",
 518                r"                 nodes={font=\small, anchor=west}] {",
 519                *[
 520                    f"            \\node [small{self.colors[j]}node, label=right:{algo_names[j]} with {attr} attributes] {{}}; \\\\"
 521                    for j in range(3)

 786    def coskySqlComparaisonLatex(self, timeDict, maxRows, maxTime, latexFilePath, scaleX=280, scaleY=280):
 787        """
 788        Create a LaTeX document that plots the execution time of CoSky SQL queries
 789        across 3, 6, and 9 attributes on a 2D graph.
 790
 791        :param timeDict: Dictionary containing execution times by number of rows.
 792        :param maxRows: Maximum number of rows considered.
 793        :param maxTime: Maximum execution time observed.
 794        :param latexFilePath: Path where the resulting LaTeX file will be saved.
 795        :param scaleX: Width of the graph in points (default 280pt).
 796        :param scaleY: Height of the graph in points (default 280pt).
 797        """
 798        self.path += latexFilePath
 799
 800        attributes = [3, 6, 9]
 801        colors = self.colors[:3]
 802        attr_names = ["3 attributes", "6 attributes", "9 attributes"]
 803
 804        # Clean and sort the dictionary keys
 805        time_dict_clean = {int(k): v for k, v in timeDict.items()}
 806        time_dict_clean = dict(sorted(time_dict_clean.items()))
 807
 808        # Find the maximum Y value across all columns
 809        global_max_time = max(
 810            max(float(row[i]) for row in time_dict_clean.values())
 811            for i in range(3)
 812        )
 813        global_max_time_rounded = smart_roundup(global_max_time)
 814
 815        heightMaxTick = scaleY * 0.8
 816        ratio_y = heightMaxTick / global_max_time_rounded
 817        ratio_x = scaleX / max(time_dict_clean.keys())
 818
 819        # Start LaTeX code
 820        self.latexCode = r"""\documentclass{article}
 821    \usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
 822    \usepackage{tikz}
 823    \usepackage{xcolor}
 824    \usepackage{graphicx}
 825    \usepackage{amsmath}
 826    \usepackage{caption}
 827
 828    \definecolor{brightmaroon}{RGB}{195,33,72}
 829    \definecolor{cyan}{RGB}{0,255,255}
 830    \definecolor{skyblue}{RGB}{135,206,235}
 831
 832    \begin{document}
 833    \begin{figure}[htbp]
 834        \centering
 835        \resizebox{.75\linewidth}{!}{
 836            \begin{tikzpicture}[line join=bevel,
 837                bigbrightmaroonnode/.style={shape=circle, fill=brightmaroon, draw=black, line width=1pt},
 838                bigcyannode/.style={shape=circle, fill=cyan, draw=black, line width=1pt},
 839                bigskybluenode/.style={shape=circle, fill=skyblue, draw=black, line width=1pt}]
 840    """
 841
 842        # Draw axes
 843        self.latexCode += f"""        % Axes
 844            \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- ({scaleX}pt, 0pt) node[anchor=north west, yshift=15pt] {{Cardinality}};
 845            \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- (0pt, {scaleY}pt) node[anchor=south] {{Response time in s}};
 846    """
 847
 848        # Draw X-axis graduations
 849        self.latexCode += "        % X-axis ticks\n"
 850        self.latexCode += "        \\foreach \\x/\\xtext in {\n"
 851        for i in range(6):
 852            step = int(scaleX * i / 5)
 853            value = int(max(time_dict_clean.keys()) * i / 5)
 854            self.latexCode += f"            {step}pt/${value}$,\n"
 855        self.latexCode = self.latexCode.rstrip(",\n") + "} {\n"
 856        self.latexCode += "            \\draw (\\x, 2pt) -- (\\x, -2pt) node[below] {\\xtext\\strut};\n        }\n"

 858        # Draw Y-axis graduations
 859        self.latexCode += "        % Y-axis ticks\n"
 860        self.latexCode += "        \\foreach \\y/\\ytext in {\n"

 862            pos = int(heightMaxTick * s / 5)
 863            val = int(global_max_time_rounded * s / 5)
 864            self.latexCode += f"            {pos}pt/${val}$,\n"
 865        self.latexCode = self.latexCode.rstrip(",\n") + "} {\n"
 866        self.latexCode += "            \\draw (2pt, \\y) -- (-2pt, \\y) node[left] {\\ytext\\strut};\n        }\n"
 867
 868        # Draw curves and points
 869        for i in range(3):
 870            color = colors[i]
 871            line = f"        \\draw[{color}, line width=2pt]"
 872            points = ""
 873            for k in time_dict_clean:
 874                x = int(round(k * ratio_x))
 875                y = int(round(time_dict_clean[k][i] * ratio_y))
 876                line += f" ({x}pt, {y}pt) --"
 877                points += f"        \\filldraw[color=black, fill={color}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);\n"
 878            self.latexCode += line.rstrip(" --") + ";\n" + points + "\n"
 879
 880        # Legend
 881        self.latexCode += r"""        % Caption
 882            \matrix [below left] at (current bounding box.north east) {
 883    """
 884        for i in range(3):
 885            self.latexCode += f"            \\node [big{colors[i]}node, label=right:CoSky 'SQL query' with {attributes[i]} attributes] {{}}; \\\\\n"
 886        self.latexCode += r"""        };
 887            \end{tikzpicture}
 888        }
 889        \caption{Execution time of CoSky 'SQL queries' with 3, 6, and 9 attributes}
 890        \label{fig:cosky_sql_comparaison}
 891    \end{figure}
 892    \end{document}"""
 893
 894        self.addLatexCode(self.latexCode)
 895        self.render()

 966        tick_count = 6
 967        self.latexCode += "            \\foreach \\x/\\xtext in {\n"
 968        for i in range(tick_count + 1):
 969            ratio = i / tick_count
 970            if is_log_x:
 971                log_val = math.log(maxRows + 1) * ratio
 972                raw_val = int(math.exp(log_val)) - 1
 973                pos = int(log_val * ratio_x)
 974            else:
 975                raw_val = int(maxRows * ratio)
 976                pos = int(scaleX * ratio)
 977
 978            if raw_val <= 0:
 979                label = "$0$"
 980            else:
 981                exponent = int(math.log10(raw_val)) if raw_val > 0 else 0
 982                base = int(raw_val / (10 ** exponent)) if exponent != 0 else raw_val
 983                label = f"${base} \\times 10^{{{exponent}}}$" if exponent > 0 else f"${raw_val}$"
 984            self.latexCode += f"                {pos}pt/{label},\n"
 985        self.latexCode = self.latexCode.rstrip(",\n") + "} {\n"
 986        self.latexCode += "                \\draw (\\x, 2pt) -- (\\x, -2pt) node[below] {\\xtext\\strut};\n            }\n"
 987
 988        # Generate Y-axis graduations
 989        y_steps = 6
 990        self.latexCode += "\n            % Y-axis ticks\n"
 991        self.latexCode += "            \\foreach \\y/\\ytext in {\n"
 992        for i in range(y_steps + 1):
 993            ratio = i / y_steps
 994            if is_log_y:
 995                log_val = math.log(maxTime + 1) * ratio
 996                val = int(math.exp(log_val)) - 1
 997                pos = int(log_val * ratio_y)
 998            else:
 999                val = maxTime * ratio
1000                pos = int(heightMaxTick * ratio)
1001            label = f"${round(val, 1)}$"
1002            self.latexCode += f"                {pos}pt/{label},\n"
1003        self.latexCode = self.latexCode.rstrip(",\n") + "} {\n"
1004        self.latexCode += "                \\draw (2pt, \\y) -- (-2pt, \\y) node[left] {\\ytext\\strut};\n            }\n"
1005
1006        # Draw the curve and points
1007        self.latexCode += "\n            % Curve and points\n"
1008        line = f"            \\draw[skyblue, line width=2pt]"
1009        points = ""
1010        for k in sorted(timeDict.keys(), key=lambda x: int(x)):
1011            x_raw = int(k)
1012            y_raw = timeDict[k][0]
1013            x = int(round(math.log(x_raw + 1) * ratio_x)) if is_log_x else int(round(x_raw * ratio_x))
1014            y = int(round(math.log(y_raw + 1) * ratio_y)) if is_log_y else int(round(y_raw * ratio_y))
1015            line += f" ({x}pt, {y}pt) --"
1016            points += f"            \\filldraw[color=black, fill=skyblue] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);\n"
1017        self.latexCode += line.rstrip(" --") + ";\n" + points
1018
1019        # Legend and caption
1020        self.latexCode += r"""
1021                % Legend
1022                \matrix [below left, draw=none] at (current bounding box.north east) {
1023                    \node [bigskybluenode, label=right:CoSky ``SQL'' with """ + str(column) + r""" attributes] {}; \\
1024                };
1025            \end{tikzpicture}
1026        }
1027        \caption{CoSky SQL: response time for """ + str(column) + r""" attributes}
1028        \label{fig:cosky_sql_response_time_""" + str(column) + r"""_attributes}
1029    \end{figure}
1030
1031    \end{document}
1032    """
1033
1034        self.addLatexCode(self.latexCode)
1035        self.render()

1038def roundtoNearestThousand(value):
1039    """
1040    Round the given value to the nearest thousand.
1041
1042    :param value: The value to round.
1043    :return: Rounded value.
1044    """
1045    if value == 0:
1046        return 0
1047    return round(value / 1000) * 1000

1050def round_up_to_multiple(value, multiple):
1051    """
1052    Round up the given value to the next multiple of 'multiple'.
1053
1054    :param value: The value to round.
1055    :param multiple: The multiple to round up to.
1056    :return: Rounded value.
1057    """
1058    return int(math.ceil(value / multiple) * multiple)
1059
1060
1061def roundtoNearestTen(value):
1062    """
1063    Round the given value to the nearest ten.
1064
1065    :param value: The value to round.
1066    :return: Rounded value.
1067    """
1068    if value == 0:
1069        return 0
1070    return round(value / 10) * 10
1071
1072
1073def roundToNearestN(value, n):
1074    """
1075    Round the given value to the nearest N.
1076
1077    :param value: The value to round.
1078    :param n: The nearest number to round to.
1079    :return: Rounded value.
1080    """
1081    if value == 0:
1082        return 0
1083    return round(value / (n - 1)) * (n - 1)
1084
1085
1086def smart_roundup(value):
1087    """
1088    Smartly round up a value to a "nice" upper bound (for axis scaling purposes).
1089
1090    :param value: The value to round up.
1091    :return: Rounded up value.
1092    """
1093    if value == 0:
1094        return 10
1095    magnitude = 10 ** (len(str(int(value))) - 1)
1096    base = (int(value) // magnitude + 1) * magnitude
1097    return base

  43    def getData(self, path):
  44        """

  47        :param path: Path to the JSON file.

  50        with open(path, 'r') as file:
  51            data = json.load(file)
  52        timeDict = data.get("time_data", {})
  53        maxRows = data.get("max_rows", 0)
  54        maxTime = data.get("max_time", 0)
  55        return timeDict, maxRows, maxTime

  57    def get_rgb_value(self, color_name):
  58        """

  63        """
  64        color_map = {

  74    def prepareComparisonData(self, jsonPaths, attributes=[3, 6, 9]):
  75        """
  76        Prepare time data for comparison plots.
  77
  78        :param jsonPaths: List of paths to JSON files.
  79        :param attributes: List of attributes to consider (default [3, 6, 9]).
  80        :return: (timeDicts, maxRowsList, maxTimeList)
  81        """
  82        timeDicts = []
  83        all_max_rows = []
  84        all_times_per_attr = [[] for _ in attributes]
  85
  86        for path in jsonPaths:
  87            timeDict, maxRows, _ = self.getData(path)
  88            timeDict = {int(k): v for k, v in timeDict.items()}
  89            timeDicts.append(timeDict)
  90            all_max_rows.append(max(timeDict.keys()))
  91
  92            for i in range(len(attributes)):
  93                print(len(attributes))
  94                all_times_per_attr[i].extend(
  95                    timeDict[k][i] for k in timeDict
  96                )
  97
  98        maxRowsList = [max(all_max_rows)] * len(attributes)
  99        maxTimeList = [max(times) for times in all_times_per_attr]
 100
 101        return timeDicts, maxRowsList, maxTimeList

 115    def twoAlgoComparaison369Latex(self, timeDict1, timeDict2, maxRowsList, maxTimeList, algo1, algo2,
 116                                   latexFilePath="", scaleX=280, scaleY=280, attributes=[3, 6, 9]):
 117        """
 118        Generate clean and well-indented LaTeX code to compare two algorithms across multiple attributes
 119        (typically for 3, 6, and 9 attributes), with linear scaling for axes.
 120
 121        :param timeDict1: Time dictionary for the first algorithm.
 122        :param timeDict2: Time dictionary for the second algorithm.
 123        :param maxRowsList: List containing the maximum cardinality for each attribute configuration.
 124        :param maxTimeList: List containing the maximum execution time for each attribute configuration.
 125        :param algo1: Enum member (AlgoEnum) representing the first algorithm to compare.
 126        :param algo2: Enum member (AlgoEnum) representing the second algorithm to compare.
 127        :param latexFilePath: Path to save the generated LaTeX file (relative or absolute).
 128        :param scaleX: Width of the graph in points (default is 280pt).
 129        :param scaleY: Height of the graph in points (default is 280pt).
 130        :param attributes: List of attribute counts to compare (default is [3, 6, 9]).
 131        """
 132        self.path += latexFilePath
 133        algo1_name = algo1.value[0]
 134        algo2_name = algo2.value[0]
 135
 136        # Define color styles
 137        color_styles = []
 138        for i, color in enumerate(self.colors[:2]):
 139            rgb = self.get_rgb_value(color)
 140            color_styles.append(f"\\definecolor{{{color}}}{{RGB}}{{{rgb}}}")
 141            color_styles.append(
 142                f"\\tikzset{{big{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},"
 143                f"\nsmall{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}}}"
 144            )
 145
 146        latex_lines = [
 147            r"\documentclass[tikz, border=10pt]{standalone}",
 148            r"\usepackage{tikz}",
 149            r"\usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta, shapes, positioning}",
 150            r"\usepackage{xcolor}",
 151            *color_styles,
 152            r"\begin{document}"
 153        ]
 154
 155        for i in range(len(attributes)):
 156            maxTime = roundtoNearestThousand(maxTimeList[i])  # Round maxTime to nearest thousand
 157            print(maxTime)
 158
 159            ratioX = scaleX / maxRowsList[i]
 160            ratioY = scaleY / maxTime
 161
 162            # Algo 1 line and points
 163            line1 = f"\\draw[{self.colors[0]}, line width=2pt]"
 164            points1 = []
 165            for k in sorted(timeDict1.keys()):
 166                x = int(round(k * ratioX))
 167                y = int(round(timeDict1[k][i] * ratioY * 0.8))
 168                line1 += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 169                points1.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={self.colors[0]}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 170            line1 = line1.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 171
 172            # Algo 2 line and points
 173            line2 = f"\\draw[{self.colors[1]}, line width=2pt]"
 174            points2 = []
 175            for k in sorted(timeDict2.keys()):
 176                x = int(round(k * ratioX))
 177                y = int(round(timeDict2[k][i] * ratioY * 0.8))
 178                line2 += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 179                points2.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={self.colors[1]}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 180            line2 = line2.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 181
 182            # Axes graduations
 183            x_axis = "        \\foreach \\x/\\xtext in {\n"
 184            for step in [scaleX * s / 5 for s in range(6)]:
 185                value = roundtoNearestTen(maxRowsList[i] * (step / scaleX))
 186                x_axis += f"            {roundtoNearestTen(step)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 187            x_axis = (x_axis.rstrip(", \n")
 188                      + "} {\n"
 189                      + "            \\draw (\\x, 2pt) -- (\\x, -2pt) node[below] {\\xtext\\strut};\n"
 190                      + "        }")
 191
 192            y_axis = "        \\foreach \\y/\\ytext in {\n"
 193            for step in [scaleY * s / 5 for s in range(5)]:
 194                adjusted_value = roundtoNearestTen(maxTime * (step / (scaleY * 0.8)))
 195                y_axis += f"            {roundtoNearestTen(step)}pt/${adjusted_value}$, \n"
 196            y_axis = (y_axis.rstrip(", \n")
 197                      + "} {\n"
 198                      + "            \\draw (2pt, \\y) -- (-2pt, \\y) node[left] {\\ytext\\strut};\n"
 199                      + "        }")
 200
 201            tikz_block = [
 202                f"    % Graph for {attributes[i]} attributes",
 203                r"    \begin{tikzpicture}[",
 204                f"        line join=bevel,",
 205                f"        big{self.colors[0]}node/.style={{shape=circle, fill={self.colors[0]}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},",
 206                f"        big{self.colors[1]}node/.style={{shape=circle, fill={self.colors[1]}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},",
 207                f"        small{self.colors[0]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[0]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}},",

 212                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- (0pt, {scaleY}pt) node[anchor=south] {{Response time in s}};",
 213                r"        % Axis graduation",
 214                x_axis,
 215                y_axis,
 216                r"        % Lines",
 217                f"        {line1}",
 218                f"        {line2}",
 219                r"        % Points",
 220                *["        " + pt for pt in points1],
 221                *["        " + pt for pt in points2],
 222                r"        % Caption",
 223                r"        \matrix [below left] at (current bounding box.north east) {",

 225                f"            \\node [small{self.colors[1]}node, label=right:{algo2_name} with {attributes[i]} attributes] {{}}; \\\\",
 226                r"        };",
 227                r"    \end{tikzpicture}"
 228            ]
 229
 230            latex_lines.extend(tikz_block)
 231
 232        latex_lines.append(r"\end{document}")
 233        self.latexCode = "\n".join(latex_lines)
 234        self.addLatexCode(self.latexCode)
 235        self.render()

 237    def twoAlgoComparaison369LatexLog(self, timeDict1, timeDict2, maxRowsList, maxTimeList, algo1, algo2,
 238                                      latexFilePath="", scaleX=280, scaleY=280, attributes=[3, 6, 9],
 239                                      scaleType="LinX/LinY"):
 240        """
 241        Generate LaTeX code to compare two algorithms across multiple attributes (3, 6, 9),
 242        with optional logarithmic or linear scaling on the X and/or Y axes.
 243
 244        :param timeDict1: Time dictionary for the first algorithm.
 245        :param timeDict2: Time dictionary for the second algorithm.
 246        :param maxRowsList: List of maximum cardinalities (number of rows) for each attribute.
 247        :param maxTimeList: List of maximum execution times for each attribute.
 248        :param algo1: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the first algorithm.
 249        :param algo2: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the second algorithm.
 250        :param latexFilePath: Path where the LaTeX output file will be saved.
 251        :param scaleX: Width of the plot in points (default 280).
 252        :param scaleY: Height of the plot in points (default 280).
 253        :param attributes: List of attributes (typically [3, 6, 9]) to generate the plots for.
 254        :param scaleType: Scaling type for axes, can be "LinX/LinY", "LogX/LinY", "LinX/LogY", or "LogX/LogY".
 255        """
 256        self.path += latexFilePath
 257        algo1_name = algo1.value[0]
 258        algo2_name = algo2.value[0]
 259
 260        # Define color styles
 261        color_styles = []
 262        for i, color in enumerate(self.colors[:2]):
 263            rgb = self.get_rgb_value(color)
 264            color_styles.append(f"\\definecolor{{{color}}}{{RGB}}{{{rgb}}}")
 265            color_styles.append(
 266                f"\\tikzset{{big{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},"
 267                f"small{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}}}"
 268            )
 269
 270        latex_lines = [
 271            r"\documentclass[tikz, border=10pt]{standalone}",
 272            r"\usepackage{tikz}",
 273            r"\usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta, shapes, positioning}",
 274            r"\usepackage{xcolor}",
 275            *color_styles,
 276            r"\begin{document}"
 277        ]
 278
 279        for i in range(len(attributes)):
 280            maxTime = roundtoNearestThousand(maxTimeList[i])  # Round maxTime to nearest thousand
 281            print(maxTime)
 282
 283            # Set the scaling type
 284            is_log_x = 'LogX' in scaleType
 285            is_log_y = 'LogY' in scaleType
 286
 287            # Calculate scaling ratios based on the chosen scale type
 288            if is_log_x:
 289                ratioX = scaleX / math.log(maxRowsList[i] + 1)  # Logarithmic scale for X
 290            else:
 291                ratioX = scaleX / maxRowsList[i]  # Linear scale for X
 292
 293            if is_log_y:
 294                ratioY = scaleY / math.log(maxTime + 1)  # Logarithmic scale for Y
 295            else:
 296                ratioY = scaleY / maxTime  # Linear scale for Y
 297
 298            # Algo 1 line and points
 299            line1 = f"\\draw[{self.colors[0]}, line width=2pt]"
 300            points1 = []
 301            for k in sorted(timeDict1.keys()):
 302                x = int(round(math.log(k + 1) * ratioX)) if is_log_x else int(round(k * ratioX))
 303                y = int(round(math.log(timeDict1[k][i] + 1) * ratioY)) if is_log_y else int(
 304                    round(timeDict1[k][i] * ratioY))
 305                line1 += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 306                points1.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={self.colors[0]}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 307            line1 = line1.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 308
 309            # Algo 2 line and points
 310            line2 = f"\\draw[{self.colors[1]}, line width=2pt]"
 311            points2 = []
 312            for k in sorted(timeDict2.keys()):
 313                x = int(round(math.log(k + 1) * ratioX)) if is_log_x else int(round(k * ratioX))
 314                y = int(round(math.log(timeDict2[k][i] + 1) * ratioY)) if is_log_y else int(
 315                    round(timeDict2[k][i] * ratioY))
 316                line2 += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 317                points2.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={self.colors[1]}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 318            line2 = line2.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 319
 320            # Axes graduations
 321            x_axis = "        \\foreach \\x/\\xtext in {\n"
 322            if is_log_x:
 323                log_steps = [math.log(s + 1) for s in range(0, maxRowsList[i] + 1, maxRowsList[i] // 5)]
 324                for step in log_steps:
 325                    value = roundtoNearestTen(math.exp(step))
 326                    x_axis += f"            {int(step * ratioX)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 327            else:
 328                for step in [scaleX * s / 5 for s in range(6)]:
 329                    value = roundtoNearestTen(maxRowsList[i] * (step / scaleX))
 330                    x_axis += f"            {int(step)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 331            x_axis = (x_axis.rstrip(", \n")
 332                      + "} {\n"
 333                      + "            \\draw (\\x, 2pt) -- (\\x, -2pt) node[below, font=\\small] {\\xtext\\strut};\n"
 334                      + "        }")
 335
 336            y_axis = "        \\foreach \\y/\\ytext in {\n"
 337            if is_log_y:
 338                log_steps = [math.log(s + 1) for s in range(0, maxTime + 1, maxTime // 5)]
 339                for step in log_steps:
 340                    adjusted_value = roundtoNearestTen(math.exp(step))
 341                    y_axis += f"            {int(step * ratioY)}pt/${adjusted_value}$, \n"
 342            else:
 343                for step in [scaleY * s / 5 for s in range(5)]:
 344                    adjusted_value = round(maxTime * (step / (scaleY * 0.8)), 2)
 345                    y_axis += f"            {int(step)}pt/${adjusted_value}$, \n"
 346            y_axis = (y_axis.rstrip(", \n")
 347                      + "} {\n"
 348                      + "            \\draw (2pt, \\y) -- (-2pt, \\y) node[left, font=\\small] {\\ytext\\strut};\n"
 349                      + "        }")
 350
 351            tikz_block = [
 352                f"    % Graph for {attributes[i]} attributes",
 353                r"    \begin{tikzpicture}[",
 354                f"        line join=bevel,",
 355                f"        big{self.colors[0]}node/.style={{shape=circle, fill={self.colors[0]}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},",
 356                f"        big{self.colors[1]}node/.style={{shape=circle, fill={self.colors[1]}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},",
 357                f"        small{self.colors[0]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[0]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}},",
 358                f"        small{self.colors[1]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[1]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}",
 359                r"    ]",
 360                r"        % Axes",
 361                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- ({scaleX}pt, 0pt) node[anchor=north west, yshift=15pt] {{Cardinality}};",
 362                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- (0pt, {scaleY}pt) node[anchor=south, font=\\large] {{Response time in s}};",
 363                r"        % Axis graduation",
 364                x_axis,
 365                y_axis,
 366                r"        % Lines",
 367                f"        {line1}",
 368                f"        {line2}",
 369                r"        % Points",
 370                *["        " + pt for pt in points1],
 371                *["        " + pt for pt in points2],
 372                r"        % Caption -",
 373                r"        \matrix [draw=none, fill=white, fill opacity=0.7, text opacity=1,",
 374                r"                 above right=0.5cm and 0cm of current bounding box.north west,",
 375                r"                 nodes={font=\small, anchor=west}] {",
 376                f"            \\node [small{self.colors[0]}node, label=right:{algo1_name} with {attributes[i]} attributes] {{}}; \\\\",
 377                f"            \\node [small{self.colors[1]}node, label=right:{algo2_name} with {attributes[i]} attributes] {{}}; \\\\",
 378                r"        };",
 379                r"    \end{tikzpicture}"
 380            ]
 381
 382            latex_lines.extend(tikz_block)
 383
 384        latex_lines.append(r"\end{document}")
 385        self.latexCode = "\n".join(latex_lines)
 386        self.addLatexCode(self.latexCode)
 387        print(self.latexCode)
 388        self.render()

 390    def threeAlgoComparaison369LatexLog(self, timeDict1, timeDict2, timeDict3, maxRowsList, maxTimeList, algo1, algo2,
 391                                        algo3,
 392                                        latexFilePath="", scaleX=280, scaleY=280, attributes=[3, 6, 9],
 393                                        scaleType="LinX/LinY"):
 394        """
 395        Generate LaTeX code to compare three algorithms across multiple attributes
 396        with optional logarithmic scaling for X and/or Y axes.
 397
 398        :param timeDict1: Time dictionary for the first algorithm.
 399        :param timeDict2: Time dictionary for the second algorithm.
 400        :param timeDict3: Time dictionary for the third algorithm.
 401        :param maxRowsList: List of maximum row counts per attribute (3, 6, 9).
 402        :param maxTimeList: List of maximum execution times per attribute (3, 6, 9).
 403        :param algo1: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the first algorithm.
 404        :param algo2: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the second algorithm.
 405        :param algo3: Enum value (AlgoEnum) corresponding to the third algorithm.
 406        :param latexFilePath: Output path where the generated LaTeX file will be saved.
 407        :param scaleX: Width of the generated graph (in pt, default 280).
 408        :param scaleY: Height of the generated graph (in pt, default 280).
 409        :param attributes: List of attributes to generate graphs for (default [3, 6, 9]).
 410        :param scaleType: Type of scaling on X and Y axes ("LinX/LinY", "LogX/LinY", "LinX/LogY", or "LogX/LogY").
 411        """
 412
 413        self.path += latexFilePath
 414        algo_names = [algo1.value[0], algo2.value[0], algo3.value[0]]
 415        timeDicts = [timeDict1, timeDict2, timeDict3]
 416
 417        # Define color styles
 418        color_styles = []
 419        for i, color in enumerate(self.colors[:3]):
 420            color_value, color_format = self.get_rgb_value(color)
 421            color_styles.append(f"\\definecolor{{{color}}}{{{color_format}}}{{{color_value}}}")
 422            color_styles.append(
 423                f"\\tikzset{{big{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=1pt}},"
 424                f"small{color}node/.style={{circle, fill={color}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}}}}"
 425            )
 426
 427        latex_lines = [
 428            r"\documentclass[tikz, border=10pt]{standalone}",
 429            r"\usepackage{tikz}",
 430            r"\usetikzlibrary{arrows.meta, shapes, positioning}",
 431            r"\usepackage{xcolor}",
 432            *color_styles,
 433            r"\begin{document}"
 434        ]
 435
 436        # Determine scaling type
 437        is_log_x = 'LogX' in scaleType
 438        is_log_y = 'LogY' in scaleType
 439
 440        for i, attr in enumerate(attributes):
 441            maxRows = maxRowsList[i]
 442
 443            maxTime = roundtoNearestThousand(maxTimeList[i])
 444
 445            ratioX = scaleX / math.log(maxRows + 1) if is_log_x else scaleX / maxRows
 446            ratioY = scaleY / math.log(maxTime + 1) if is_log_y else scaleY / maxTime
 447
 448            # Generate lines and points
 449            lines = []
 450            points = []
 451            for j, timeDict in enumerate(timeDicts):
 452                color = self.colors[j]
 453                line = f"\\draw[{color}, line width=2pt]"
 454                point_set = []
 455                for k in sorted(timeDict.keys()):
 456                    x = int(round(math.log(k + 1) * ratioX)) if is_log_x else int(round(k * ratioX))
 457                    yval = timeDict[k][i]
 458                    y = int(round(math.log(yval + 1) * ratioY)) if is_log_y else int(round(yval * ratioY))
 459                    line += f"({x}pt, {y}pt) -- "
 460                    point_set.append(f"\\filldraw[color=black, fill={color}] ({x}pt, {y}pt) circle (2pt);")
 461                line = line.rstrip(" -- ") + ";"
 462                lines.append(line)
 463                points.append(point_set)
 464
 465            # X axis graduations
 466            x_axis = "        \\foreach \\x/\\xtext in {\n"
 467            if is_log_x:
 468                log_steps = [math.log(s + 1) for s in range(0, maxRows + 1, max(1, maxRows // 5))]
 469                for step in log_steps:
 470                    value = roundtoNearestTen(math.exp(step))
 471                    x_axis += f"            {int(step * ratioX)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 472            else:
 473                for step in [scaleX * s / 5 for s in range(6)]:
 474                    value = roundtoNearestTen(maxRows * (step / scaleX))
 475                    x_axis += f"            {int(step)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 476            x_axis = (
 477                    x_axis.rstrip(", \n") +
 478                    "} {\n            \\draw (\\x, 2pt) -- (\\x, -2pt) node[below, font=\\small] {\\xtext\\strut};\n        }"
 479            )
 480
 481            # Y axis graduations
 482            y_axis = "        \\foreach \\y/\\ytext in {\n"
 483            if is_log_y:
 484                log_steps = [math.log(s + 1) for s in range(0, maxTime + 1, max(1, maxTime // 5))]
 485                for step in log_steps:
 486                    value = roundtoNearestTen(math.exp(step))
 487                    y_axis += f"            {int(step * ratioY)}pt/${value}$, \n"
 488            else:
 489                for step in [scaleY * s / 5 for s in range(6)]:
 490                    adjusted_value = round(maxTime * (step / (scaleY * 0.8)), 2)
 491                    y_axis += f"            {int(step)}pt/${adjusted_value}$, \n"
 492            y_axis = (
 493                    y_axis.rstrip(", \n") +
 494                    "} {\n            \\draw (2pt, \\y) -- (-2pt, \\y) node[left, font=\\small] {\\ytext\\strut};\n        }"
 495            )
 496
 497            tikz_block = [
 498                f"    % Graph for {attr} attributes",
 499                r"    \begin{tikzpicture}[",
 500                r"        line join=bevel,",
 501                *[
 502                    f"        small{self.colors[j]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[j]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}},"
 503                    for j in range(3)
 504                ],
 505                r"    ]",
 506                r"        % Axes",
 507                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- ({scaleX}pt, 0pt) node[anchor=north west, yshift=15pt] {{Cardinality}};",
 508                f"        \\draw[-stealth] (0pt, 0pt) -- (0pt, {scaleY}pt) node[anchor=south, font=\\large] {{Response time in s}};",
 509                r"        % Axis graduation",
 510                x_axis,
 511                y_axis,
 512                r"        % Lines",
 513                *["        " + l for l in lines],
 514                r"        % Points",
 515                *[f"        {pt}" for point_set in points for pt in point_set],
 516                r"        % Caption",
 517                r"        \matrix [draw=none, fill=white, fill opacity=0.7, text opacity=1,",
 518                r"                 above right=0.5cm and 0cm of current bounding box.north west,",
 519                r"                 nodes={font=\small, anchor=west}] {",
 520                *[
 521                    f"            \\node [small{self.colors[j]}node, label=right:{algo_names[j]} with {attr} attributes] {{}}; \\\\"
 522                    for j in range(3)
 523                ],
 524                r"        };",
 525                r"    \end{tikzpicture}",
 526                r"\clearpage"
 527            ]
 528
 529            latex_lines.extend(tikz_block)
 530
 531        latex_lines.append(r"\end{document}")
 532        self.latexCode = "\n".join(latex_lines)
 533        self.addLatexCode(self.latexCode)
 534        self.render()

 754                    f"        small{self.colors[j]}node/.style={{circle, fill={self.colors[j]}, draw=black, line width=0.5pt, minimum size=4pt, inner sep=0pt}},"

104        """
105        Round the given value to the nearest multiple of (n-1).
106
107        :param value: The value to round.

def smart_roundup(value): 
1087def smart_roundup(value):
1088    """
1089    Smartly round up a value to a "nice" upper bound (for axis scaling purposes).
1090
1091    :param value: The value to round up.
1092    :return: Rounded up value.
1093    """
1094    if value == 0:
1095        return 10
1096    magnitude = 10 ** (len(str(int(value))) - 1)
1097    base = (int(value) // magnitude + 1) * magnitude
1098    return base
